The paper deals with the problem of quantizing channel state information for beamforming in a multiple-antenna fading channel, which is a classic problem in information theory and communication systems (cs.IT, cs.COMM). The focus is on the design of variable-length quantizers, which is a topic in signal processing and coding theory (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the power constraint of the transmitter, which is a topic in wireless networking and optimization (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes several extensions to the main result, which could potentially fall under the category of networked systems and control (cs.NI).
